        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    Which day trip from Agadir is the most popular?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Essaouira</strong> is consistently the most popular full-day trip, followed closely by <strong>Paradise Valley</strong> for half-day excursions.</p>
                    <p><strong>Why Essaouira is #1:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>UNESCO World Heritage site with stunning architecture</li>
                        <li>Beautiful coastal setting with beach ramparts</li>
                        <li>Famous for Game of Thrones filming location</li>
                        <li>Excellent seafood restaurants at the harbor</li>
                        <li>Artisan workshops and unique shopping opportunities</li>
                        <li>Perfect blend of culture, history, and beach relaxation</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Why Paradise Valley is #2:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Closest destination (just 45 minutes away)</li>
                        <li>Incredible natural beauty with crystal pools</li>
                        <li>Perfect for families and active travelers</li>
                        <li>Great value at €35 for half-day adventure</li>
                        <li>Can be combined with afternoon activities</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>For first-time visitors, we recommend doing both if you have time!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    Can I do multiple day trips in one visit to Agadir?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Absolutely! In fact, we highly recommend it.</strong> Most travelers do 2-4 day trips during their Agadir stay.</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>Recommended Combinations:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>3-4 Days in Agadir:</strong> City tour + Paradise Valley + One major trip (Essaouira or Marrakech)</li>
                        <li><strong>1 Week:</strong> 3-4 day trips + beach days + desert activities (quad, camel)</li>
                        <li><strong>10+ Days:</strong> All major destinations plus relaxation time</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Smart Planning Tips:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Alternate between easy/hard days (e.g., Marrakech followed by beach day)</li>
                        <li>Do half-day trips (Paradise Valley) in morning, relax afternoon</li>
                        <li>Save long trips (Marrakech, Tafraout) for when you're not jet-lagged</li>
                        <li>Book 2-3 trips in advance, leave flexibility for weather</li>
                        <li>Most trips can be scheduled any day except some attractions closed Mondays</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Package Deals:</strong> Ask about multi-trip discounts when booking 3+ excursions!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    Is Marrakech worth visiting from Agadir as a day trip?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Yes, but with realistic expectations!</strong> Marrakech is Morocco's most famous city and absolutely worth seeing, but it's a long day.</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>The Reality:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>3 hours drive each way through beautiful Atlas Mountains</li>
                        <li>12-13 hour total day (early departure 7-8 AM)</li>
                        <li>5-6 hours actual time in Marrakech (rushed but doable)</li>
                        <li>You'll see highlights but not everything in detail</li>
                        <li>Can be tiring, especially in summer heat</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>What You'll See:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Koutoubia Mosque (exterior, iconic 77m minaret)</li>
                        <li>Bahia Palace (stunning architecture and gardens)</li>
                        <li>Souks and medina (vibrant markets)</li>
                        <li>Jemaa el-Fnaa square (UNESCO site, street performers)</li>
                        <li>Lunch at traditional restaurant</li>
                        <li>Time for shopping and photos</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Our Recommendation:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>If you have 1 week or less:</strong> Skip Marrakech, focus on closer destinations</li>
                        <li><strong>If you have 7-10+ days:</strong> Marrakech day trip is worthwhile bucket-list experience</li>
                        <li><strong>Best option:</strong> Consider 2-day Marrakech trip with overnight stay (we can arrange!)</li>
                        <li><strong>Alternative:</strong> Taroudant offers similar medina/souk experience in just 1.5 hours</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p>Many travelers are happy they did it, but some wish they'd spent more time in closer destinations like Essaouira or Paradise Valley.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    What's the best day trip for families with children?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Paradise Valley</strong> is hands-down the best family day trip! Here's why:</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>Why Kids Love Paradise Valley:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Swimming in natural pools (safe, shallow areas available)</li>
                        <li>Adventure element (hiking, exploring, nature)</li>
                        <li>Short drive (45 minutes - kids won't get restless)</li>
                        <li>Active and engaging (not boring museum-style tour)</li>
                        <li>Cliff jumping optional for older adventurous kids (8+)</li>
                        <li>Packed lunch picnic style makes it fun</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Other Great Family Options:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Souss Massa National Park:</strong> Wildlife spotting, flamingos, birds (educational and fun)</li>
                        <li><strong>Taroudant:</strong> Shorter trip (1.5hrs), easy walking, kids enjoy ramparts and souks</li>
                        <li><strong>Essaouira:</strong> Beach town with activities, but long drive (3 hours)</li>
                        <li><strong>Crocoparc (Agadir area):</strong> Not a day trip, but kids LOVE the crocodiles!</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Trips to Avoid with Young Kids:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Marrakech:</strong> Too long (12+ hours), exhausting for children under 8</li>
                        <li><strong>Tafraout:</strong> Long drive, limited child-friendly activities</li>
                        <li><strong>Sidi Ifni:</strong> Long journey, not much for kids to do</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Family-Friendly Features We Offer:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Child car seats available (free, just request when booking)</li>
                        <li>Flexible stops for bathroom breaks and snacks</li>
                        <li>Kid-friendly lunch options</li>
                        <li>Patient guides experienced with families</li>
                        <li>Adjusted pace to accommodate children's energy levels</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Children under 5 are usually free or heavily discounted on most tours!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    Do day trip prices include lunch and entrance fees?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>It varies by tour - always check what's included!</strong> Here's the typical breakdown:</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>Usually INCLUDED in Price:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Transportation in comfortable air-conditioned vehicle</li>
                        <li>Hotel pickup and drop-off (all Agadir hotels)</li>
                        <li>Professional English/French-speaking guide</li>
                        <li>Fuel and driver costs</li>
                        <li>Bottled water during transport</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Lunch:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Paradise Valley:</strong> Bring your own or buy from local cafes (€5-10)</li>
                        <li><strong>Essaouira:</strong> Free time for lunch at harbor (€10-15 seafood recommended)</li>
                        <li><strong>Marrakech:</strong> Usually included at traditional restaurant</li>
                        <li><strong>Atlas Mountains/Berber Villages:</strong> Home-cooked lunch usually included</li>
                        <li><strong>Other trips:</strong> Check individual tour details</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Entrance Fees:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Marrakech:</strong> Bahia Palace €7, other sites extra</li>
                        <li><strong>Souss Massa:</strong> Park entry ~€2-3 per person</li>
                        <li><strong>Paradise Valley:</strong> Small local guide tip expected (€1-2)</li>
                        <li><strong>Essaouira:</strong> No entrance fees (open medina)</li>
                        <li><strong>Taroudant:</strong> No entrance fees</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Optional Extras (Not Included):</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Personal shopping and souvenirs</li>
                        <li>Alcoholic drinks with meals</li>
                        <li>Tips for guide and driver (appreciated but not required)</li>
                        <li>Optional activities (e.g., horse carriage ride in Taroudant €5-10)</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Typical Total Budget Per Person:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Paradise Valley: €35 tour + €10 snacks = €45 total</li>
                        <li>Essaouira: €45 tour + €15 lunch = €60 total</li>
                        <li>Marrakech: €50 tour (lunch included) + €10 entries = €60 total</li>
                        <li>Taroudant: €35 tour + €10-12 lunch = €47 total</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Always carry cash (dirhams) for personal expenses - many places don't accept cards!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    Can I customize a private day trip itinerary?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Absolutely! Private tours are fully customizable.</strong> This is one of the biggest advantages of booking with a local guide.</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>What You Can Customize:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Departure Time:</strong> Start when you want (no early wake-up if you don't want!)</li>
                        <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Shorter or longer than standard tours</li>
                        <li><strong>Itinerary:</strong> Add or skip stops based on your interests</li>
                        <li><strong>Pace:</strong> Spend more time where you want, skip what doesn't interest you</li>
                        <li><strong>Lunch Spot:</strong> Choose restaurants or picnic locations</li>
                        <li><strong>Photo Stops:</strong> Extra time for photography at scenic spots</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Popular Custom Combinations:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Paradise Valley + Immouzer Waterfall:</strong> Double nature experience</li>
                        <li><strong>Essaouira + Argan Cooperatives:</strong> Culture + local products</li>
                        <li><strong>Taroudant + Berber Village:</strong> Combined cultural immersion</li>
                        <li><strong>Coastal Tour:</strong> Legzira + Sidi Ifni + Tiznit in one long day</li>
                        <li><strong>Photography Tour:</strong> Multiple scenic stops for serious photographers</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Private Tour Pricing:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Based on 2-4 people minimum (more cost-effective with more people)</li>
                        <li>Usually 30-50% more than group tours but with total flexibility</li>
                        <li>Worth it for couples, families, or those with specific interests</li>
                        <li>Example: Private Essaouira tour €120-180 for 2-4 people vs €45pp group tour</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Special Interest Private Tours:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Photography Tours:</strong> Best spots, golden hour timing, composition help</li>
                        <li><strong>Food Tours:</strong> Market visits, street food, cooking demonstrations</li>
                        <li><strong>Shopping Tours:</strong> Best places for carpets, leather, argan products with negotiation help</li>
                        <li><strong>Surf Exploration:</strong> Multiple surf spots in Taghazout/Tamri area</li>
                        <li><strong>Birdwatching:</strong> Specialized routes for ornithologists</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>How to Book Custom Tours:</strong></p>
