                    <ul>
                        <li>Number of people</li>
                        <li>Preferred destinations</li>
                        <li>Special interests or requirements</li>
                        <li>Any dietary restrictions or accessibility needs</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>We'll create a custom itinerary and price quote within 24 hours!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    What's the best season for day trips from Agadir?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Good news: Agadir has 300+ days of sunshine, so day trips work year-round!</strong> But each season has advantages:</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>🌸 Spring (March-May) - BEST OVERALL</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Weather:</strong> Perfect 20-25°C, comfortable for all activities</li>
                        <li><strong>Highlights:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Almond blossoms in valleys (February-March) - spectacular!</li>
                                <li>Wildflowers in mountains</li>
                                <li>Waterfalls at full flow (Immouzer best now)</li>
                                <li>Not too hot for Marrakech or desert trips</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Best Trips:</strong> Paradise Valley, Immouzer, Atlas Mountains, Marrakech</li>
                        <li><strong>Downsides:</strong> Peak season means higher prices and more tourists</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>☀️ Summer (June-August) - HOT BUT MANAGEABLE</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Weather:</strong> Hot 25-35°C inland, cooler on coast</li>
                        <li><strong>Highlights:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Coastal trips very pleasant (Essaouira 5-10°C cooler than Agadir)</li>
                                <li>Beach destinations at their best</li>
                                <li>Paradise Valley perfect for swimming</li>
                                <li>Long daylight hours</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Best Trips:</strong> Essaouira, Sidi Ifni, Paradise Valley, coastal routes</li>
                        <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Marrakech (can be 40°C+), midday desert trips</li>
                        <li><strong>Tip:</strong> Book early morning departures to beat the heat</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>🍂 Fall (September-November) - EXCELLENT CHOICE</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Weather:</strong> Ideal 22-28°C, still warm but not hot</li>
                        <li><strong>Highlights:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Perfect for all types of trips</li>
                                <li>Fewer crowds than spring</li>
                                <li>Harvest season in valleys</li>
                                <li>Great for photography (clear skies)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Best Trips:</strong> All destinations work perfectly</li>
                        <li><strong>Downsides:</strong> None really - this is secretly the best season!</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>❄️ Winter (December-February) - MILD & AFFORDABLE</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Weather:</strong> Mild 15-20°C, can be cooler in mountains</li>
                        <li><strong>Highlights:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Lowest prices of the year</li>
                                <li>Fewest tourists (except Christmas/New Year)</li>
                                <li>Waterfalls flowing from rain</li>
                                <li>Almond blossoms start in February</li>
                                <li>Perfect for cultural city tours</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Best Trips:</strong> Taroudant, Essaouira, Marrakech, cultural tours</li>
                        <li><strong>Consider:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Paradise Valley water very cold (still beautiful to visit)</li>
                                <li>Mountain trips can be cold - bring layers</li>
                                <li>Occasional rain (5-10 days/month max)</li>
                                <li>Some waterfalls best now (but cold water)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Month-by-Month Best Picks:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Jan-Feb:</strong> City tours, Essaouira, Marrakech (cooler is better)</li>
                        <li><strong>Mar-May:</strong> Everything! Peak season for all destinations</li>
                        <li><strong>Jun-Aug:</strong> Coastal trips, Paradise Valley swimming</li>
                        <li><strong>Sep-Nov:</strong> All trips excellent, fewer crowds</li>
                        <li><strong>Dec:</strong> Cultural tours, shopping trips, city exploration</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Our Recommendation:</strong> April-May or September-October for the absolute best weather and experience!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    How far in advance should I book day trips?
                    <span class="faq-icon">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>It depends on the season and destination, but generally 3-7 days ahead is ideal.</strong></p>
                    
                    <p><strong>Book 1-2 Weeks in Advance If:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Traveling during peak season (March-May, October-November)</li>
                        <li>Visiting during holidays (Christmas, New Year, Easter)</li>
                        <li>Want specific departure times or private tours</li>
                        <li>Traveling with a large group (6+ people)</li>
                        <li>Planning popular trips on weekends (Essaouira, Paradise Valley)</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Book 3-5 Days Ahead If:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Traveling during shoulder season (June-September, December-February)</li>
                        <li>Flexible with dates and times</li>
                        <li>Small group (2-4 people)</li>
                        <li>Booking group tours (usually available)</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Last-Minute Booking (1-2 Days):</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Usually Available:</strong> Taroudant, Souss Massa, local trips</li>
                        <li><strong>Sometimes Available:</strong> Paradise Valley, Essaouira (weekdays)</li>
                        <li><strong>Rarely Available:</strong> Marrakech, popular weekend trips</li>
                        <li><strong>Note:</strong> Last-minute prices usually same, but limited vehicle choice</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Same-Day Booking:</strong></p>
                    <p>Possible for some trips but not recommended:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Very limited availability</li>
                        <li>May not get preferred language guide</li>
                        <li>Risk of missing out entirely</li>
                        <li>Contact us before 8 AM for same-day possibilities</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Our Booking Recommendation:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Before you arrive:</strong> Book 1-2 "must-do" trips (Essaouira, Marrakech)</li>
                        <li><strong>After arrival:</strong> Book other trips 3-5 days ahead based on weather</li>
                        <li><strong>Leave flexibility:</strong> Don't book every single day - weather, energy levels matter</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Cancellation Policy:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Free cancellation up to 24 hours before departure (most tours)</li>
                        <li>Full refund if trip cancelled due to weather</li>
                        <li>Reschedule flexibility during your stay</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Pro Tips:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Book via WhatsApp for fastest confirmation (+212 645 792 457)</li>
                        <li>We can hold spots for 24-48 hours without payment</li>
                        <li>Multi-trip discounts available when booking 3+ excursions</li>
                        <li>Weather forecasts 5-7 days out usually accurate for planning</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

